From: burakgon <burakgon12@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH libinput] quirks: Add PixArt I2C-HID 093A:4F05 haptic touchpad

The 2026 ASUS ExpertBook Ultra (B9406CAA) ships a PixArt I2C-HID haptic
touchpad with VID:PID 093A:4F05 (ACPI ASCP1D80). The kernel's
hid-multitouch parser reports an inflated ABS_MT_PRESSURE max for this
device — observed kernel-reported max is 2601 (the same value as the
Y-axis logical max) while the real hardware pressure range tops out
around 1000.

Real touch pressure values fall into 5..150 typically, which on the
inflated 2601 scale is well below libinput's pressure activation
threshold. libinput consequently rejects every motion as
'kernel bug: Touch jump detected and discarded' and the cursor never
moves on the user's display.

Workaround is identical to the Asus UX302LA entry already in
50-system-asus.quirks: tell libinput to ignore the pressure axes
entirely on this device (BTN_TOUCH is reliable, libinput uses that for
touch state), so the broken pressure scale stops driving false-jump
verdicts.

Tested on ASUS ExpertBook Ultra B9406CAA. With the quirk active the
cursor responds normally to light touches; without it, no motion
registers at all.

Signed-off-by: burakgon <burakgon12@gmail.com>
---
 quirks/30-vendor-pixart.quirks | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/quirks/30-vendor-pixart.quirks b/quirks/30-vendor-pixart.quirks
--- a/quirks/30-vendor-pixart.quirks
+++ b/quirks/30-vendor-pixart.quirks
@@ -22,3 +22,12 @@
 MatchVendor=0x093A
 MatchProduct=0x1336
 AttrEventCode=-BTN_RIGHT
+
+# ASUS ExpertBook Ultra B9406CAA (2026)
+# Kernel mis-reports ABS_MT_PRESSURE max; ignore pressure entirely.
+[Pixart Touchpad (093A:4F05)]
+MatchBus=i2c
+MatchUdevType=touchpad
+MatchVendor=0x093A
+MatchProduct=0x4F05
+AttrEventCode=-ABS_MT_PRESSURE;-ABS_PRESSURE;
